President Trump addressed members of the military during a Christmas conference call from Mar-a-Lago in Florida. He expressed his appreciation for their service and highlighted the accomplishments of different branches of the armed forces. He also discussed the strong state of the U.S. economy and recent trade deals. President Trump responded to questions about potential pardons, impeachment, and North Korea. He mentioned the possibility of a signing ceremony for the U.S.-China trade deal with Chinese President Xi Jinping.